import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import seaborn as sns # Sentiment distribution plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6)) sns.countplot(x='Sentiment', data=df) plt.title('Distribution of Sentiments') plt.xlabel('Sentiment') plt.ylabel('Frequency') plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right') plt.show() # Numerical features vs. Sentiment numerical_features = ['Retweets', 'Likes'] plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6)) for i, feature in enumerate(numerical_features): plt.subplot(1, 2, i + 1) sns.boxplot(x='Sentiment', y=feature, data=df) plt.title(f'{feature} vs. Sentiment') plt.xlabel('Sentiment') plt.ylabel(feature) plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right') plt.tight_layout() plt.show() # Correlation matrix correlation_matrix = df[numerical_features].corr() plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6)) sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot=True, cmap='coolwarm') plt.title('Correlation Matrix of Numerical Features') plt.show() # Grouped statistics print(df.groupby('Sentiment')[numerical_features].agg(['mean', 'median', 'std']))

Data visualization

Subtask:

Create visualizations to better understand the data.

Reasoning: Create visualizations for the distribution of the target variable, relationships between numerical features and the target variable, and relationships between categorical features and the target variable.

In [4]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt import seaborn as sns # Sentiment distribution plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6)) sns.countplot(x='Sentiment', data=df) plt.title('Distribution of Sentiments') plt.xlabel('Sentiment') plt.ylabel('Frequency') plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right') plt.show() # Numerical features vs. Sentiment numerical_features = ['Retweets', 'Likes'] plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6)) for i, feature in enumerate(numerical_features): plt.subplot(1, 2, i + 1) sns.boxplot(x='Sentiment', y=feature, data=df) plt.title(f'{feature} vs. Sentiment') plt.xlabel('Sentiment') plt.ylabel(feature) plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right') plt.tight_layout() plt.show() # Categorical features vs. Sentiment categorical_features = ['Platform', 'Country'] plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6)) for i, feature in enumerate(categorical_features): plt.subplot(1, 2, i + 1) sns.countplot(x=feature, hue='Sentiment', data=df) plt.title(f'Sentiment Distribution by {feature}') plt.xlabel(feature) plt.ylabel('Frequency') plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right') plt.tight_layout() plt.show()
